subject: Strange decorator in Eclipse
msgSnippet: Running some tests and a clump of them have a blue arrow decorator rather than the usual green checkbox (Eclipse).  Have attached figure as JunitFigure.jpg.
messageBody: Running some tests and a clump of them have a blue arrow decorator rather than the usual green checkbox (Eclipse). Have attached figure as JunitFigure.jpg. If I run this class by itself as a JUnit test, it runs fine. But notice that there is a different decorator and there are no execution times, so I believe these tests simply did not run.
